    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>New York</placeName>
                <date>June 8<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1859</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p>
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">You are aware I suppose that my pros-<lb/>pects of obtaining the
                situation in <placeName>Baltimore</placeName><lb/> are for the present frustrated.
                By the last<lb/> letter I received from them I have been informed<lb/> that the
                funds raised by annual subscription is<lb/> found to be insufficient to cover the
                necessary<lb/> expenses and the meeting therefore resolved for<lb/> performing their
                service and not to engage a<lb/> minister until they shall be better enabled<lb/> to
                do so. <persName>Mr. Carvalho</persName> will meanwhile<lb/> act as Hazan.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">It is now my intention to apply for the vacant<lb/> office by the
                congregation Sheareth Israel<lb/>
                <placeName>Charleston</placeName>, and would for that purpose beg your<lb/> kindness
                to use your influence in my favor<lb/> on that congregation. If you can,
                without<lb/> infringing upon either conscience or pleasure;<lb/> give me a
                recommending certificate stating<lb/> my ability and character I shall be
                greatly<lb/> obliged to you and remain as ever</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">Yours truly</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">
                <persName role="author">Mr de Solla</persName>
            </p>
            <p>Address <placeName>No 12 Hester cor Suffolk</placeName></p>
        </body>
    </text>
